Abstract

Find differentially expressed genes per cell type between dpi14 and CTR conditions.

PART 2: Infection characteristic

Visualization for infection

Infection rate is substantially different by cell type

DimPlot(obj, group.by = "cellType", split.by = "Infection")

infect_rate <- obj@meta.data %>% group_by(cellType, Infection) %>% count()
ggplot(infect_rate, aes(x = cellType, y = n, fill = Infection)) + geom_col(position='fill')

S.Score and G2M.Score are higher for infected cells

VlnPlot(obj, c("S.Score", "G2M.Score"), group.by = "Infection")

Statistics for infection

Chi-square test to see if distribution of infected cells prefer a certain cell type. p < 0.05 means that there is an association between cell types and infection.

infect_wide <- tidyr::spread(infect_rate, cellType, n) %>% tibble::column_to_rownames(var = "Infection")
chisq.test(infect_wide)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  infect_wide
## X-squared = 30.113, df = 3, p-value = 1.307e-06

Infected cells have higher score for cell cycle

t.test(S.Score ~ Infection, data = obj@meta.data)

PART 3: Differential Expression

Differential expression for each cell type, bewteen infected and uninfected at day 14

diff_egos <- list()
for (ct in unique(obj$cellType)) {
  subObj <- subset(obj, subset = cellType == ct & dpi == 'd14')
  subObj <- SetIdent(subObj, value = "Infection")
  
  diff_egos[[ct]] <- get_diff.f(object = subObj, ident1 = "Infected", ident2 = "Uninfected", padj_cut = 0.05, fc_cut = 0)
}

saveRDS(diff_egos, file = paste0("diff_egos_IvsU.RDS"))

Differential expression for each cell type, bewteen uninfected day 0 and day 14 (This will elucidate clues about paracrine signal, or secondary effect from viral infection)

diff_egos2 <- list()
for (ct in unique(obj$cellType)) {
  subObj <- subset(obj, subset = cellType == ct & Infection == 'Uninfected')
  subObj <- SetIdent(subObj, value = "dpi")
  
  diff_egos2[[ct]] <- get_diff.f(object = subObj, ident1 = "d14", ident2 = "ctrl", padj_cut = 0.05, fc_cut = 0)
}

saveRDS(diff_egos2, file = paste0("diff_egos_D14vs0.RDS"))
